{"SALUBRIOUS":[{"def":"Favorable to health; healthful; promoting health; as, salubrious air, water, or climate.","pos":""}],"SALUBRITY":[{"def":"The quality of being salubrious; favorableness to the preservation of health; salubriousness; wholesomeness; healthfulness; as, the salubrity of the air, of a country, or a climate.","pos":""}],"SALUE":[{"def":"There was no \"good day\" and no saluyng.","pos":""}],"SALUTARY":[{"def":"Wholesome; healthful; promoting health; as, salutary exercise.","pos":""},{"def":"Promotive of, or contributing to, some beneficial purpose; beneficial; advantageous; as, a salutary design.","pos":""}],"SALUTATION":[{"def":"The act of saluting, or paying respect or reverence, by the customary words or actions; the act of greeting, or expressing good will or courtesy; also, that which is uttered or done in saluting or greeting.","pos":""}],"SALUTATORIAN":[{"def":"The student who pronounces the salutatory oration at the annual Commencement or like exercises of a college, -- an honor commonly assigned to that member of the graduating class who ranks second in scholarship.","pos":""}],"SALUTATORILY":[{"def":"By way of salutation.","pos":""}],"SALUTATORY":[{"def":"Containing or expressing salutations; speaking a welcome; greeting; -- applied especially to the oration which introduces the exercises of the Commencements, or similar public exhibitions, in American colleges.","pos":""}],"SALUTE":[{"def":"To honor, as some day, person, or nation, by a discharge of cannon or small arms, by dipping colors, by cheers, etc.","pos":""}],"SALUTER":[{"def":"One who salutes.","pos":""}],"SALUTIFEROUS":[{"def":"Bringing health; healthy; salutary; beneficial; as, salutiferous air.","pos":""}],"SALUTIFEROUSLY":[{"def":"Sal`u*tif\"er*ous*ly, adv.","pos":""}]}